# Cursor instructions for SMART-ERP-API

These rules help AI coding agents work effectively in this .NET 10 Web API using Onion + DDD + CQRS, MediatR, EF Core, and Swagger.

## Architecture overview
- Solution layout: API (exposes endpoints), Application (CQRS, validators, services), Domain (entities/settings, no dependencies), Infrastructure (EF Core, repositories).
- Data access: EF Core DbContext in `SMART.ERP.Infrastructure/DatabaseContext.cs` with NoTracking by default. Many entities and relationships are configured in `OnModelCreating` with Restrict deletes.
- CQRS: Requests handled via MediatR. Commands/Queries live under `SMART.ERP.Application/Features/**` (per entity feature folder). Controllers in API layer call MediatR only.
- API base: Controllers inherit from `SMART.ERP.API/Controllers/BaseApiController.cs` which provides `Mediator` and route `api/v{version}/[controller]`.
- Cross-cutting:
  - Validation: FluentValidation via pipeline `ValidationBehavior<,>` (`Application/Behaviours/ValidationBehavior.cs`). Throw `Application.Exceptions.ValidationException` on failures.
  - Error handling: `ErrorHandlerMiddleware` serializes `Application.Wrappers.Response<T>` and maps exceptions to HTTP codes; Sentry captures unhandled/DB errors.
  - Versioning & Swagger: API Versioning is configured in `Program.cs` with grouped Swagger per version; `ConfigureSwaggerOptions` and `SwaggerDefaultValues` included.
  - Caching: `AddStackExchangeRedisOutputCache` + `AddOutputCache` policies in `Program.cs` (e.g., `cache_products`, `cache_categories`, etc.). Tag and vary by query.
  - Realtime: SignalR hubs at `hub/notification` (JWT-authorized) and `hub/chat`, with JWT support via query string (`?access_token=`).

## Conventions and patterns
- Controllers:
  - Attribute routes already include version segment; define `[ApiVersion("1.0")]` on controllers and keep thin: map HTTP to `Mediator.Send(new ...Command/query)`.
  - Return wrapper types `Application.Wrappers.Response<T>` or paged wrappers found in `Application/Wrappers`.
- Features (CQRS):
  - Per Domain entity, create a `Features/<Entity>/` folder with subfolders `Commands` and `Queries`.
  - Command/Query classes implement `IRequest<Response<...>>`; handlers depend on abstractions (repositories/services), not DbContext directly.
  - Validate with FluentValidation: add `AbstractValidator<TRequest>` in same folder; pipeline enforces automatically.
- Data access:
  - Prefer `Application.Repository.IRepositoryAsync<T>` (Ardalis.Specification). Concrete impl is registered as `CustomRepositoryAsync<>` in DI.
  - For read models, consider `IReadRepositoryAsync<T>` and Specifications under `Application/Specifications`.
- Mapping: Use AutoMapper profiles in `Application/Mappings` to map Domain to DTOs in `Application/DTOs/**`.
- Caching: When modifying resources covered by an output cache policy, evict by tag using `IOutputCacheStore.EvictByTagAsync("cache_products", ...)`.
- Auth: JWT configured in `Application/ServiceExtensions.cs` from `appsettings`. For SignalR, token can be passed via `?access_token=`.

## Integration points and settings
- Configuration: `SMART.ERP.API/appsettings*.json` for ConnectionStrings (Database, Redis, AzureBlobStorage), JWTSettings, MailSettings, MetaSettings, GoogleCalendar.
- Accounting (double-entry, live in prod): auto-posting via `IAccountingPostingService` (`Application/Services/AccountingPostingService/`); domain entities `JournalEntry`/`JournalEntryLine`, `LedgerAccount`, `AccountingMapping` (`AccountMappingKey` enum), `CostCenter`, `FiscalPeriod`/`FiscalYear`. Posting is idempotent via `SourceDocumentType`/`SourceDocumentId`.
- Jobs: Quartz scheduled jobs registered in `Application/ServiceExtensions.cs` (`RecurringInvoiceJob`, `RevenueRecognitionJob`, `AdvisorGoalJob`, `LongLivedOpportunitiesJob`, `LogSessionJob`). Use cron expressions there.
- Reports: QuestPDF for PDF (`Infrastructure/Services/QuotationPdfService`), ClosedXML for Excel (`Infrastructure/Services/KardexReportService`).
- External services: Azure Blob Storage (`BlobServiceClient`), MailKit, Google Calendar, Meta (Facebook/WhatsApp) APIs, RestSharp, Sentry.

## Developer workflow
- Build/run: Open the solution `SMART.ERP.sln`. Default profile serves at `https://localhost:7211` and `http://localhost:5211` with Swagger at `/swagger` (`API/Properties/launchSettings.json`).
- Local DB: `appsettings.Development.json` points the `Database` connection at a remote production server by default — switch it to your local SQL Server before running locally.
- Migrations/DB: EF Core DbContext is in Infrastructure. Create migrations in the Infrastructure project so the `DatabaseContext` is the target.
- Testing: Not present in repo. When adding features, include unit tests in a new test project if needed; follow CQRS boundaries.
- Debugging:
  - Errors are normalized by `ErrorHandlerMiddleware`; database errors return user-friendly Spanish messages; check Sentry for details.
  - API versioning: Swagger UI lists one doc per version group (`v1`, `v2`). Ensure new controllers declare `[ApiVersion]` and routes match.
- CORS/WebSockets: CORS allows `*.vercel.app`, `smartbusiness.site`, and localhost. WebSockets origins must be listed in `Program.cs`.

## Examples
- Create a query handler skeleton:
  - File: `Application/Features/Product/Queries/GetProductById/GetProductByIdQuery.cs`
  - Pattern: `record GetProductByIdQuery(int Id) : IRequest<Response<ProductDto>>;` and handler uses `IReadRepositoryAsync<Product>` + AutoMapper to return `Response<ProductDto>`.
- Controller action skeleton:
  - Inherit `BaseApiController`, decorate controller with `[ApiVersion("1.0")]` and route defaults, then `return Ok(await Mediator.Send(new GetProductByIdQuery(id)));`

## Quality bar for contributions
- Respect layer boundaries (API -> MediatR -> Application -> Repository/Services -> Infrastructure). Domain remains dependency-free.
- Use Response<T> wrappers and validations; surface meaningful messages in Spanish to align with existing responses.
- When adding endpoints likely to be cached, add/align OutputCache policies and evict tags on writes.
